SIMPLE: fractional
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fractional
<hw>Frac"tion*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to fractions or a fraction; constituting a fraction; <as>as,
<ex>fractional</ex> numbers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Relatively small; inconsiderable; insignificant;
<as>as, a <ex>fractional</ex> part of the population</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fractional crystallization</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>,
<cd>a process of gradual and approximate purification and separation, by
means of repeated solution and crystallization therefrom.</cd> --
<col><b>Fractional currency</b></col>, <cd>small coin, or paper notes,
in circulation, of less value than the monetary unit.</cd> --
<col><b>Fractional distillation</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a
process of distillation so conducted that a mixture of liquids,
differing considerably from each other in their boiling points, can be
separated into its constituents.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fractionally</ent>⟦br⟧
